Here is the cleaned up text:

Einstein Bots is available in Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience. Setup for Einstein Bots is available in Lightning Experience.
Available in: Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions


To build and manage Einstein Bots:
Customize Application
OR
Modify Metadata
OR
Manage Bots

Open the bot you want to use as the destination for this block.
On the dialog menu, click the plus icon, and then select Import a Block.
Select the block from the list of available blocks. Then click Next.
Review the block details and rename it to fit your bot. Then click Next.
Resolve any included goals into your bot by creating a new goal or mapping to an existing goal. Click Next.
Confirm mappings to the block variables. New variables are created by default, but you can choose to map them to existing variables instead. Click Next.
Click Finish.

Your block is created as a dialog group in your bot. The dialog group counts towards your total allowed dialog groups in your bot version.

After you import a block into your bot, it turns into a dialog group and is no longer connected to the block template. Updates to the block template donâ€™t affect the dialog group created from the block.

Some blocks require additional customization. See Explore the Einstein Bot Block Library.

To remove a dialog group created from a block, click the dropdown next to the dialog group name and select Ungroup. The dialog group is deleted and all dialogs part of that group are listed in the main dialog listing.
title: Importing Einstein Bot Blocks
